{"task": "question_answering", "output": "No, a heart attack and cardiac arrest are not the same thing. A heart attack is caused by a blockage in one or more of the coronary arteries, which supply blood to the heart muscle. This deprives part of the heart muscle of oxygen and can cause it to become damaged or die. In contrast, a cardiac arrest is when the heart suddenly stops beating, usually due to an electrical malfunction. This causes the person to lose consciousness and stop breathing."}

The concept of grinding peanuts into a paste can be traced back to the Aztecs and Incas in pre-Columbian Mesoamerica. In the late 1800s, various peanut paste products were marketed in the United States, and in 1904, Dr. John Harvey Kellogg patented a process for making peanut butter.
